@node MenuProgramAbout "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ About..."

Selecting  the  About  menu choice brings up a dialog box containing the 
version   of   the   CheckItOut!   program,   a   copyright   notice and 
registration information. 

If  you  are  using  the evaluation version of the program, that fact is 
stated  in  the  dialog  box  along  with  the following gadgets: @{b}AGREE@{ub}, 
@{b}REGISTRATION@{ub},    and    @{b}CANCEL@{ub}.    If    you    don't    agree   to  the 
@{"license and warranty" link Copyright}   information   outlined  in  this  document, press 
CANCEL  and  don't use the program. If you do agree with the license and 
warranty press AGREE to continue.

If  you  have registered and need to enter the registration information, 
select  REGISTRATION.  This  will  open  another dialog box containing a 
form  to  enter the registration information. Registration requires that 
you  agree  to  the  license  and  warranty  and that you pay a software 
license  fee.  See  the  section on @{"Registration" link Registration} for more information on 
how to register.

If  you  are  a registered user, the dialog box registration information 
contains your name and serial number.


The keyboard shortcut key for @{i}About...@{ui} is to press <Right-Amiga-A>.

@endnode

@node MenuProgramCloseWindow "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ Close Window"

Selecting  the  Close  Window  menu performs the same action as pressing 
the   Close-Window-Gadget,   that  is  it  closes  the  currently active 
account or category list.

To exit the program, select @{"Quit" link menuProgramQuit} from the Program menu.


The keyboard shortcut key for @{i}Close Window@{ui} is to press <Right-Amiga-C>.

@endnode

@node MenuProgramNewAccount "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ New Account..."

This  menu  choice  allows  you to create a new account. When you select 
@{i}New  Account@{ui},  a  fill-in  form  is  displayed.  Choose  the appropriate 
account type:

  Bank        -- Use this type for accounts that you get regular
                 statements for.  For example, a checking account or
                 mutual fund account.

  Cash        -- Use the cash type for passbook bank accounts and
                 for other simple cash monitoring.  This type is
				 useful for a business petty cash account.

  Asset       -- Use asset accounts to manage things of value such
                 as property.

  Credit Card -- This type of account is for a charge card account
                 like a MasterCard or Visa.

  Liability   -- Use this account to monitor liabilities like a home 
                 mortgage or car loan.

After  you  have  chosen the account type, enter a name for the account. 
Names  can  be  up to 15 characters long. You may also enter an optional 
description  for  the account. Account descriptions can be 49 characters 
long.  When  the account information entry is complete, press <Enter> or 
select [Record] to actually create the account.

A   number   of  @{"Shortcut Keys" link SpecialKeysGeneric }  can  be  used  to  modify  the  name and 
description text fields in this form.

When   you   create  an  account,  CheckItOut!  automatically  creates a 
transfer  category  using  the account name surrounded by brackets (e.g. 
an   account   named  @{b}@{u}Checking@{uu}@{ub}  has  a  corresponding  transfer category 
@{b}[Checking]@{ub}).   CheckItOut!   also   adds   the   account   name   to the 
@{"Open Account" link MenuProgramOpenAccount } menu list.

 Note: The account list is ordered alphabetically and the first ten 
       accounts are assigned shortcut keys.  If you change the name of
	 an account, it may change the assignment of the shortcut keys.

After  the  account  is created, a new register window will open for the 
account  with  a  pre-filled  transaction  waiting  for  you to enter an 
opening  balance.  Bank,  cash  and asset accounts default to an initial 
deposit.  Credit  card and liability accounts expect an initial debit to 
be  entered.  You  can  change this by <Tab> or <Shift-Tab> to the other 
field.  You  can also change any of the other fields in the transaction. 
When  the  opening  balance  entry  is complete, press <Enter> or select 
[Record]  to  complete  account  creation.  Below  is  an  example  of a 
opening balance transaction.


 +-------------------------------------------------------------------+
 |DATE | NUMBER |  DESCRIPTION  |  PAYMENT | DEPOSIT  | `/ | BALANCE |
 |     |-------------------------------------------------------------+
 |     |        CATEGORY        |         MEMO             |         |
 +-------------------------------------------------------------------+
 @{fg shine}|12/01|        |Opening Balance|@{bg fill}          |      0.00@{bg background}|    |     0.00|
 |     |-------------------------------------------------------------+
 |1994 |[Account Name]          |                          |         |
 +-------------------------------------------------------------------+@{fg text}

@endnode

@node MenuProgramOpenAccount "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ Open Account..."

Once  you  have  created some accounts, the @{i}Open Account@{ui} menu contains a 
sub-menu  item  for  each  account. Choosing one of the account names in 
the   sub-menu  causes  the  register  window  for  that  account  to be 
displayed.   The   first   ten   accounts   also   contain  shortcut key 
selections.   For   example,  you  can  quickly  open  first  account by 
pressing  <Right-Amiga-1>  The  tenth  account can be opened by pressing 
<Right-Amiga-0>.

Program
   +-----------------+
   |About...         |     
   |Close Window     |  
   |-----------------|
   |New Account...   |     
   |@{fg fill}@{bg text}Open Account...  @{fg text}@{bg background}+-----------------+
   |Change Account...| Cash      @{i}@{fg background}@{bg text} A @{fg text}@{bg background} 1@{ui} |
   |Delete Account   | Checking  @{i}@{fg background}@{bg text} A @{fg text}@{bg background} 2@{ui} |
   |-----------------| IRA       @{i}@{fg background}@{bg text} A @{fg text}@{bg background} 3@{ui} |
   |New File...      | Property  @{i}@{fg background}@{bg text} A @{fg text}@{bg background} 4@{ui} |
   |Open File...     | Saving    @{i}@{fg background}@{bg text} A @{fg text}@{bg background} 5@{ui} |
   |-----------------| Visa      @{i}@{fg background}@{bg text} A @{fg text}@{bg background} 6@{ui} |
   |Import...        +-----------------+
   |Export...        |     
   |Print...         |     
   |-----------------|
   |Quit             |     
   +-----------------+


@endnode

@node MenuProgramChangeAccount "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ Change Account..."

This  menu  choice  allows  you  to modify account information. When you 
select  @{i}Change  Account@{ui}, a fill-in form is displayed. You can choose the 
account type from the following choices:

  Bank        -- Use this type for accounts that you get regular
                 statements for.  For example, a checking account or
                 mutual fund account.

  Cash        -- Use the cash type for passbook bank accounts and
                 for other simple cash monitoring.  This type is
                 useful for a business petty cash account.

  Asset       -- Use asset accounts to manage things of value such
                 as property.

  Credit Card -- This type of account is for a charge card account
                 like a MasterCard or Visa.

  Liability   -- Use this account to monitor liabilities like a home 
                 mortgage or car loan.

Account  names  can be up to 15 characters long. You may also change the 
optional  description  for  the  account. Account descriptions can be 49 
characters   long.   When   the   account   information  modification is 
complete, press <Enter> or select [Record] to store the changes.

A   number   of  @{"Shortcut Keys" link SpecialKeysGeneric }  can  be  used  to  modify  the  name and 
description text fields in this form.

If  you  change  the account name, CheckItOut! automatically changes the 
transfer  category  for the account and all transfers to the account are 
updated  to  reflect  the  new  category.  The account name will also be 
changed in the @{"Open Account" link MenuProgramOpenAccount } menu list.

 Note: The account list is ordered alphabetically and the first ten 
       accounts are  assigned shortcut keys.  If you change the name 
       of an account, it may change the assignment of the shortcut 
       keys.

@endnode

@node MenuProgramDeleteAccount "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ Delete Account"

Use  this  menu  choice  if  you  need to delete an entire account. This 
function  is  very  destructive  and  can not be undone. You should only 
delete  an  account  when  you  are  confident  you  will  not  need the 
transaction  history  any more. The following Program Alert is displayed 
prior  to  the  delete  function to give you a last chance to cancel the 
operation.

@{b}Make  @{u}SURE@{uu}  the  account  name displayed in the requester is the account 
you want to delete!@{ub}

 +------------------------------------+
 |                                    |
 |                                    |
 |  Deleting an Account is Permanent  |
 |        and Irreversible.           |
 |                                    |
 | All Transactions in Account @{b}[Name]@{ub} |
 |  Will be Deleted and any Transfers |
 |  to the Account Will be Converted  |
 |    to No Category Transactions.    |
 |                                    |
 |                                    |
 |                                    |
 | [Ok]                      [Cancel] |
 |                                    |
 +------------------------------------+

@endnode

@node MenuProgramNewFile "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ New File..."

You  can  create  a  new  set of accounts by selecting this menu item. A 
file  requester  is displayed prompting you to enter a new name for your 
accounts   database.   The   default   file  extensions  for CheckItOut! 
database  files  are @{u}.cio@{uu}. When a new database file is created, a set of 
default  categories  is  created  as  well.  CheckItOut!  looks  for the 
default   category   file   named   @{u}DefaultCategories.qif@{uu}   in  the same 
directory  as  the  program.  After the new database is created, you can 
begin creating your accounts.

Normally,  you  don't  need  to  create  a  new  file,  instead  use the 
@{"New Account..." link MenuProgramNewAccount }   menu   choice   to  add  new  accounts  to  an existing 
database.  Instances  where  you  may  want  to create separate database 
file  include  when  you  run a business that maintains separate account 
information or if you manage bank accounts for others (like your kids).

@endnode

@node MenuProgramOpenFile "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ Open File..."

You  can  change  to  a different set of accounts by selecting this menu 
item.  A  file requester is displayed prompting you to choose a database 
file.  The  default  file  extension  is  @{u}.cio@{uu}  for CheckItOut! database 
files. Select the desired directory and database file name.

@endnode

@node MenuProgramImport "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ Import..."

By  selecting  this  menu  item,  you can import account transactions or 
categories  created  by  CheckItOut!  or other personal finance programs 
like  Quicken  or Microsoft Money. You must first select the destination 
account  using  @{"Open Account" link MenuProgramOpenAccount }  the  @{b}Program@{ub}  menu  If  you want to import 
categories, select @{"Categories & Transfers" link MenuProgramOpenAccount } from the @{b}View@{ub} menu.

A  file  requester is displayed prompting you to choose the import file. 
The  default  file  extension is @{u}.qif@{uu} for CheckItOut! and Quicken import 
files. Select the desired directory and file name.

If  you  import  transactions  that  include  transfers to accounts that 
don't  exist,  the  transfer category is changed from @{u}[Name]@{uu} to @{u}*[Name]@{uu}. 
By  doing  this,  you  can quickly recognize that an account needs to be 
created   to   receive  these  transfers.  After  you  have  created the 
account,  you  must  go  back  and  change  the @{u}*[Name]@{uu} to @{u}[Name]@{uu} in the 
transfer transactions.

If  you  import  transactions  that duplicate an existing transaction in 
the  account,  a  warning  is  displayed in the register information box 
and the transaction is ignored.

@endnode

@node MenuProgramExport "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ Export..."

By  selecting  this  menu  item,  you can export account transactions or 
categories  created  by  CheckItOut! in a format that is compatible with 
other  personal  finance  programs  like Quicken or Microsoft Money. You 
must  first  select  the  source  account  using  @{"Open Account" link MenuProgramOpenAccount }  from the 
@{b}Program@{ub}    menu    If    you    want   to   export   categories,  select 
@{"Categories & Transfers" link MenuProgramOpenAccount } from the @{b}View@{ub} menu.

A  file  requester  is  displayed  prompting you to enter an export file 
name.  The  default  file  extension is @{u}.qif@{uu} for CheckItOut! and Quicken 
import   files.  Select  the  desired  directory  and  file  name. press 
<Enter> or select [Ok] create the export file.

@{b}Make  sure  you  do not use the same file name as your database file. If 
you do, you will corrupt your transaction database!@{ub}

@endnode

@node MenuProgramPrint "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Program/ Print"

The  action  performed  by  selecting  this  item depends on the current 
activity.  If the active window is  an  account  register,  the contents 
of the account  register  will be printed. If the active window  is  the 
category &  transfer  list,  the  list  will  be  printed.  If  you  are 
displaying one of the reports generated by CheckItOut!, that report will 
be printed. When you select @{b}Print@{ub}, the following form containing the  
page  size and the destination for the report is displayed:

 +---------------------------------+
 |                                 |
 |        --- Date Range ---       |
 |                                 |
 |      +--------+     +---------+ |
 | From |        |  To |         | |
 |      +--------+     +---------+ |
 |                                 |
 |---------------------------------|
 |                                 |
 |            +------------------+ |
 | [o] Device |@|      PRT:      | |
 |            +------------------+ |
 |                                 |
 |            +--+ +-------------+ |
 | [_] File   |fr| |PRT:         | |
 |            +--+ +-------------+ |
 |                                 |
 |---------------------------------|
 |                                 |
 |            --- Page ---         |
 |                                 |
 |         +----+           +----+ |
 |   Width |    |    Length |    | |
 |         +----+           +----+ |
 |                                 |
 | [ Ok ]              [ Cancel ]  |
 +---------------------------------+

If the active window is a check register, you can  enter  a  date  range 
in those fields.  If the active  window  context  is  a  report  or  the 
category window.  The from and to date range fields are inactive.


Choices for the device are:

 +------------------+
 |@|      SER:      | -- The serial device.
 +------------------+

 +------------------+
 |@|      PAR:      | -- The parallel device.
 +------------------+

 +------------------+
 |@|      PRT:      | -- The printer device (Recommended).
 +------------------+

 +------------------+
 |@|T:CheckItOut.txt| -- A disk file named 'T:CheckItOut.txt'
 +------------------+

If  you  choose  File,  the  [fr]  button  brings  up  the standard file 
requester.  From  the requester you can choose the destination text file 
for  the  report.  @{b}Make  sure  you do not use the same file name as your 
database file. If you do, you will @{u}DESTROY@{uu} your transaction database!@{ub}

Below  the  device choice is the page size information. CheckItOut fills 
in  a  default  page  width based on the report being displayed. You can 
customize  the  size  of  the page by entering a new page width and page 
length.

The keyboard shortcut key for @{i}Print@{ui} is to press <Right-Amiga-P>.


