@node MenuReportsItemizeByCategory "CheckItOut!: Menu/ Reports/ Itemize By Category"

When  you  select  the  @{b}Itemize by Category@{ub} report, the @{"Find Transaction" link FindTransactions } 
form  is  displayed.  Filling in fields in the displayed query form will 
limit which transactions are included in the report.

The  Itemize  by  Category  report  shows  a  detailed  list  of all the 
transactions  that  met  the  search  criteria  you  entered  in the find 
transaction  query  form.  There  are subtotals for each category. There 
are  totals  for  income,  expenses, transfers, and categories that have 
no type specified. There is a grand total at the end of the report.

You   can  @{i}double  click@{ui}  on  a  transaction  to  activate  that account 
register and select the transaction.

Use  the  arrow keys or scroll bars to move around in the report window. 
You  can  use  @{"<Right-Amiga-P>" link MenuProgramPrint }  to output the report to the printer or a 
file.  Resizing  the  window will cause more information to be displayed 
in the account, description, and memo fields.

